    "Definition in ethical codes and relevance.",
    "AI systems have the potential to manipulate and influence human behaviour in ways that are not easily detectable.",
    "AI systems must, therefore, follow human-centric design principles and leave meaningful opportunities for human choice and intervention.",
    "Such systems should not be able to unjustifiably subordinate, coerce, deceive, manipulate, condition or herd humans (EUHLEX, 2019, p. 16).",
    "Human oversight thus refers to the capability for human intervention in every decision cycle of the AI system and the ability of users to make informed, autonomous decisions regarding AI systems."
